# File ini kontrol line endings + diff behavior per file type di Git.
# Tanpa ini, Git di Windows dengan `core.autocrlf=true` convert semua
# text file ke CRLF di working tree, yang by-pass `text eol=lf` per-file
# rule di .gitattributes (kalau ada conflict antara global & per-file,
# .gitattributes menang — tapi autocrlf bisa reverse-convert lagi saat
# `git checkout` di Windows).
#
# Untuk .sql files specifically: line endings HARUS konsisten (LF)
# karena sqlx::migrate pakai SHA384 checksum dari raw bytes. CRLF vs LF
# = checksum beda = drift error "migration was previously applied but
# has been modified". Hal yang sama akan berlaku untuk semua binary-ish
# text file yang dipakai tool untuk checksum (lock files, manifests, etc).
#
# `text eol=lf` → paksa LF di working tree & commit, regardless of OS.
# `text` saja (no eol) → biarkan normalization sesuai platform (LF di
# Linux/Mac, CRLF di Windows).
#
# Reference: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitattributes

# --- Database migrations: WAJIB LF (sqlx::migrate checksum) -----------
*.sql text eol=lf

# --- Source code: biarkan platform decide (no eol specified) ---------
*.ts text
*.tsx text
*.js text
*.jsx text
*.rs text
*.py text
*.go text
*.java text
*.yml text
*.yaml text
*.json text
*.md text
*.sh text
*.toml text
*.css text
*.scss text
*.html text

# --- Binary files (jangan di-convert) --------------------------------
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.tgz binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
